delegates.body:
This delegate can rewrite parsing of schemas. __SchemaBuilder__ uses this delegate.

```javascript
// Some route with Schema
F.route('/url/', some_action1, ['post', '*MySchema']);
F.route('/url-group/', some_action2, ['post', '*MyGroup/MySchema']);

// Example
F.onSchema = function(req, group, name, callback) {

    // Here you can create validation, transformation and whatever you want

    // callback(err, newmodel);
    // callback --> rewrites req.body

    callback(null, req.body);
};```

This delegate compiles custom content in views `@{compile jade}....@{end}`. This function has to return a string. The __context__ `this === controller` is a current controller.

###Â Example

```javascript
F.onCompileView = function(name, html, model) {
    // this === controller

    if (name === 'handlebars') {
        var template = Handlebars.compile(html);
        return template(model);
    }

    if (name === 'jade') {
        var template = jade.compile(html);
        return template(model);
    }

    if (name === 'Tangular') {
        var template = Tangular.compile(html);
        return template(model);
    }

    return html;
};```

