api.body:
This class supports sending emails via SMTP protocol. `FrameworkMail` supports TLS.

- [Example: Email send](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/email-send)
- [Example: Controller email](https://github.com/totaljs/examples/tree/master/controller-mail)

```js
// Mail === Global object
var message = new Mail.Message('subject', 'body');
// or
// var message = Mail.create('subject', 'body');

// Set email sender
message.from('my@email.com', 'Peter Sirka');

message.to('friend@email.com');
message.to('family@message.com');

message.send('smtp.yourserver.com');
```

##Â How to send multiple messages?

```js
var a = new Mail.Message('subject', 'body');
var b = new Mail.Message('subject', 'body');
var c = new Mail.Message('subject', 'body');

a.to('friend@email.com');
a.from('me@email.com');

b.to('friend@email.com');
b.from('me@email.com');

c.to('friend@email.com');
c.from('me@email.com');

Mail.send('smtp.yourserver.com', [a, b, c]);
```

##Â How to check whether the SMTP server does work?

```js
Mail.try('smtp.yourserver.com', function(err) {
    if (!err)
        console.log('SMTP SERVER WORKS CORRECTLY');
});```

