## Websocket connection is disconnected after 1 minute

Certainly you use __NGINX__. The problem is in `proxy_read_timeout`:
<http://nginx.org/en/docs/http/ngx_http_proxy_module.html#proxy_read_timeout>

---

## Prevention for multiple requesting

If the server doesn't reply quickly, then the web browser can send the request again. We recorded the problem in __Chrome__ web browser.

### Total.js prevention

```javascript
exports.install = function() {
	// Prevention for multipe requests from one browser
	ROUTE('/', delay_operation, ['delay']);
};

function delay_operaiton() {
	var self = this;

	console.log('I am here.');

	setTimeout(function() {
		self.view('some-view');
	}, 10000);
}
```

### Important change for nginx

```lua
http {
	# VERY IMPORTANT FOR "DELAY" FLAG
	proxy_http_version 1.1;
}
```

## Too many open files

If the framework throws `Too many open files` exception then we have to enable [default_maximum_file_descriptors](#api~FrameworkConfiguration~default_maximum_file_descriptors) or increase the system limit via terminal `$ ulimit -v unlimited`.

```html
// The framework opens max. 10 files together and waits while they are not closed.
default_maximum_file_descriptors        : 10
```

